        "Recipe_Name": "Twice-Baked Potatoes",
        "Link": "https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/twice-baked-potatoes",
        "Ingredients": "['4 large russet potatoes', '2 tablespoons vegetable oil', '½ cup sour cream', '¼ cup unsalted butter', '¼ cup finely chopped fresh chives', '1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh tarragon (optional)', 'Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper']",
        "Instructions": "['Place a rack in middle of oven; preheat to 425°. Poke potatoes all over with a fork; rub with oil. Bake directly on oven rack until very soft when squeezed and skins are crisp, 50–60 minutes. Let cool just until you can hold them.', 'Using a serrated knife, slice potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop flesh into a medium bowl. Add sour cream, butter, chives, and tarragon (if desired); season generously with salt and pepper.', 'Divide among 4 potato skin halves, piling gloriously high—don’t pack too tightly. (And what about the leftover skins? We say add butter and salt and snack on them.)', 'Increase oven temperature to 450°. Bake potatoes on a rimmed baking sheet until filling is puffed and browned in spots, 20–25 minutes.']",
